claim.claim-text:
14. A reduced-size vehicle having a front section, a mid-section and a rear section positioned successively adjacent to one another between a front end and a rear end, and left and right sides extending between the front and rear ends, the reduced-size vehicle comprising:
a first strut portion extending generally through the mid-section from the front section to the rear section;
a second strut portion extending generally through the mid-section from the front section to the rear section, wherein the first strut portion is positioned generally higher than the second strut portion, and the second strut portion is at least indirectly coupled to the first strut portion;
a third strut portion extending outward toward at least one of the left and right sides relative to the first strut portion, wherein the third strut portion is coupled at least indirectly to at least one of the first and second strut portions, and forms a loop that is situated substantially within the front section; and
an internal compartment positioned within an internal cavity defined at least in part by the third strut portion, wherein the internal compartment extends at least 45% of a distance between the first and second strut portions.

19. A reduced-size vehicle having a wheelbase and a front section, a rear section, and a mid-section extending between the front and rear sections, wherein a central axis of the vehicle extends between front and rear ends of the vehicle, the reduced-size vehicle comprising:
a first strut portion extending generally through the mid-section from the front section to the rear section;
a second strut portion extending generally through the mid-section from the front section to the rear section, wherein the first strut portion is positioned generally higher than the second strut portion, and the second strut portion is at least indirectly coupled to the first strut portion;
a third strut portion that is coupled at least indirectly to at least one of the first and second strut portions, and is configured to form a first loop that is situated substantially within the front section;
a fourth strut portion that is coupled at least indirectly to at least one of the first and second strut portions, and is configured to form a second loop that is situated substantially within the rear section;
a first storage compartment positioned substantially within the front section of the vehicle, within the first loop; and
a second storage compartment positioned substantially within the rear section of the vehicle, within the second loop;
wherein a sum of a first length of the first storage compartment measured along the central axis and a second length of the second storage compartment measured along the central axis is greater than 50% of the wheelbase.

21. A reduced-size vehicle having a wheelbase and a front section, a rear section, and a mid-section extending between the front and rear sections, wherein a central axis of the vehicle extends between front and rear ends of the vehicle, the reduced-size vehicle comprising:
an internal cavity;
a first shock absorber;
a second shock absorber, wherein the internal cavity is positioned between the first shock absorber and the second shock absorber, and extends along more than fifty percent of the length of the first shock absorber when fully-extended; and
a first storage compartment positioned within the internal cavity, wherein under operating circumstances a first center of gravity of the vehicle is at or above a second center of gravity of the first storage compartment when empty or completely filled with a homogeneous material.

22. The reduced-size vehicle of claim 21, further comprising:
a first strut portion extending generally through the mid-section from the front section to the rear section;
a second strut portion extending outward toward at least one of the left and right sides relative to the first strut portion, wherein the second strut portion is coupled at least indirectly to the first strut portion, wherein the second strut portion forms at least one of a loop portion and a c-bracket portion, and wherein the second strut portion at least partially defines the internal cavity.
